<subSubSection id="C36C6506FFC7FFDD09C99E4B4AA23799" pageId="13" pageNumber="60" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BC9368DFFC7FFDD09C99E4B4AA23799" blockId="13.[151,1437,1355,1775]" pageId="13" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis id="B902EA9FFFC7FFDD09C99E4B4A2A3732" bold="true" box="[151,273,1355,1380]" pageId="13" pageNumber="60">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of this species can be recognized by the mesosternum less than twice the length of the metasternum and a pair of elongate posterolateral projections of the pygophore (
<figureCitation id="134D2A08FFC7FFDD0D1B9E6E4FA637D1" box="[1093,1181,1390,1415]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 45" captionStartId="13.[151,264,986,1009]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,654,965]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,654,965]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 45. Terminal abdominal segments of male Eotrechus. (40) E. elongatus, (41) E. hygropetricus, (42) E. kalidasa, (43) E. petraeus, (44) E. romglao, (45) E. siamensi s." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/287067/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="60">
Fig. 
<number id="3DBE24AAFFC7FFDD0D209E6F4FA637D1" box="[1150,1181,1391,1415]" pageId="13" pageNumber="60" value="42.0">42</number>
</figureCitation>
), whereas those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C764D0EFFC7FFDD0CDA9E704A3F37FA" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Eotrechus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elongatus">
<emphasis id="B902EA9FFFC7FFDD0CDA9E704A3F37FA" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="60">E. elongatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have the pygophore without posterolateral projections and those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C764D0EFFC7FFDD0AA99E944F4F37FA" box="[1015,1140,1427,1452]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Eotrechus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="romglao">
<emphasis id="B902EA9FFFC7FFDD0AA99E944F4F37FA" box="[1015,1140,1427,1452]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="60">E. romglao</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a pair of small knoblike lateral projections.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36C6506FFC7FFDD09999EDB4A6234F1" pageId="13" pageNumber="60" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC9368DFFC7FFDD09999EDB4A6234F1" blockId="13.[151,1437,1355,1775]" pageId="13" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis id="B902EA9FFFC7FFDD09999EDB4A7737A2" bold="true" box="[199,332,1499,1524]" pageId="13" pageNumber="60">Discussion.</emphasis>
This species has been reported from 
<collectingCountry id="F361761DFFC7FFDD0BB49EDB481D37A2" box="[746,806,1499,1524]" name="India" pageId="13" pageNumber="60">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F361761DFFC7FFDD0A6F9EDC489B37A2" box="[817,928,1500,1524]" name="Myanmar" pageId="13" pageNumber="60">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="F361761DFFC7FFDD0A879EDB4F0637A2" box="[985,1085,1499,1524]" name="Thailand" pageId="13" pageNumber="60">Thailand</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE74B7CFFC7FFDD0D149EDB4E3C37A2" author="Andersen" box="[1098,1287,1499,1524]" pageId="13" pageNumber="60" refString="Andersen, N. M. (1982 b) Semiterrestrial water striders of the genera Eotrechus Kirkaldy and Chimarrhometra Bianchi (Insecta, Hemiptera, Gerridae). Steenstrupia, 9, 1 - 25." type="journal article" year="1982" yearSuffix="b">
Andersen 
<number id="3DBE24AAFFC7FFDD0DE09EDB4FC337A2" box="[1214,1272,1499,1524]" pageId="13" pageNumber="60" value="1982.0">1982</number>
b
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE74B7CFFC7FFDD0C4C9EDB4A143441" author="Vitheepradit" pageId="13" pageNumber="60" refString="Vitheepradit, A. &amp; Sites, R. W. (2007) A review of Eotrechus Kirkaldy (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Gerridae) of Thailand with descriptions of three new species. Zootaxa, 1478, 1 - 19." type="journal article" year="2007">
Vitheepradit &amp; Sites 
<number id="3DBE24AAFFC7FFDD09AC9EFF4A143441" box="[242,303,1535,1559]" pageId="13" pageNumber="60" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The 
<collectingCountry id="F361761DFFC7FFDD082B9EFE4A933441" box="[373,424,1534,1559]" name="Thailand" pageId="13" pageNumber="60">Thai</collectingCountry>
record was based on a single winged male caught in a malaise trap on a trail near a small creek in Phu Hin Rongkla NP (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE74B7CFFC7FFDD08AB9D23481A346D" author="Vitheepradit" box="[501,801,1571,1596]" pageId="13" pageNumber="60" refString="Vitheepradit, A. &amp; Sites, R. W. (2007) A review of Eotrechus Kirkaldy (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Gerridae) of Thailand with descriptions of three new species. Zootaxa, 1478, 1 - 19." type="journal article" year="2007">
Vitheepradit &amp; Sites 
<number id="3DBE24AAFFC7FFDD0BBA9D23481A346D" box="[740,801,1571,1595]" pageId="13" pageNumber="60" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). We have attempted to collect this species several times from 
<number id="3DBE24AAFFC7FFDD098A9D474A523409" box="[212,361,1607,1631]" pageId="13" pageNumber="60" value="2011.0" valueMax="2012.0" valueMin="2010.0">
<date id="FFC8104DFFC7FFDD098A9D474A523409" box="[212,361,1607,1631]" pageId="13" pageNumber="60" value="2010" valueMax="2012">2010 to 2012</date>
</number>
at that locality and adjacent areas, including a nearby creek. However, no additional specimens were collected. So far, in 
<collectingCountry id="F361761DFFC7FFDD08EB9D6B492234D2" box="[437,537,1643,1668]" name="Thailand" pageId="13" pageNumber="60">Thailand</collectingCountry>
this species has not been collected anywhere other than in Phu Hin Rongkla NP in Loei Province.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
